Homosexuality was decriminalized in China in 1997, but discrimination against members of the LGBT community is said to be widespread.
Because of the conservative values of the country, studies have estimated that 70-90% of men who have sex with men eventually marry women.
Many of the transmissions of the disease are due to insufficient protection in sexual intercourse in these relationships.
